node.text:
Why network marketing?

The friendships. 

My home is covered in photos and photos and photos and photos of these amazing people who have come into my life. 

For the people I knew before network marketing, we are closer than ever. 

For many they are new. 

Regardless of if they are no longer in business or if they are, our friendships are so strong. 😭❤️

I am so grateful for the people. I am so grateful for LIFELONG friendships. I am so grateful for the diversity of the people in my life and in my heart. 

I always felt like the weird one out that people didn’t understand.

That was until NWM ❤️❤️❤️

Forever thankful. 

Have you ever felt like you’re looking for your humans? If so drop a smile below 😊 

#bosslee

node.text:
My little fighter.

Today I went in with her to what I thought was pre-op for her cancer removal surgery. 

She had a mast cell tumor removed five years ago from the same spot and I thought it would just be another normal surgery. 

We got there and found out now we need to go to an oncologist. Don’t know if it’s fortunate or unfortunate but it’s looking like chemo and radiation and maybe still a surgery too 😩😑

I suppose it would be silly to say that a lot of my success is because of her. But I do have to give Wookiee Lee props. 

From the day I got her she had me up at the crack of dawn. If you are not patient with her you are going to be upset at yourself LOL she is so damn cute and it is pretty much Wookiee’s way or the highway 🤣

Speaking of the highway, her newest most favorite past time is riding in her Lamborghini in the backseat sitting pretty watching TV while the car grumbles underneath of her butt LOL

If you’re a praying person please throw some up for our little baby cow. 

Mama loves you, you resilient little thing, you ❤️

#bosslee #wookieelee

The first time I shared this was about 11 years ago. I was drowning. I was working in the lab after graduating college and going more broke every two weeks. But for some reason I still told social media I would be the first millionaire in my family.

it does not have to make sense. But having a vision works.

Drop YES below to affirm this ❤️
#bosslee

node.text:
Why network marketing?

For everything it’s provided OUTSIDE of network marketing and my ability to dream huge. 

When I started this journey in 2011 it all started needing $300 a month. I was driving a 2003 Ford focus ZX3 with a hatchback and it was mint green with a stick shift because it was so much cheaper that way. I used to put it in neutral and coast down hills in Maryland to save gas. 😯 

I was asked to make a dream board at one of my first events ever and to be honest I am positive I rolled my eyes at the lady. However, for some reason I went home and I did it. I suppose that’s because one of the most important parts of network marketing success is to be coachable.

In the center of my dream board was a white Range Rover with almond interior. I don’t even know why I cut it out. I definitely did not actually care about it.

However, as five years went by and I moved from direct sales into network marketing in 2016 I bought that exact range rover. In 2017 I wrapped that Range Rover in chrome rose gold. 

I keep making these boards. And I keep living out every single one of the things I put on there.

Dreaming bigger. That’s why network marketing.

My life is a vision.

Have you ever made a dream board??
#bosslee

node.text:
Call me mama shark. 

well, you don’t have to. But a lot of our team does. ❤️❤️

serious, loving, loyal, protective. Intimidating to people who don’t understand.

and hunted by some for no reason.

@kiha_kaina thank you always for this tattoo. It means so much to me.

In Hawaiian culture we say our ancestors come back in physical forms but it’s their spirit. The ‘aumakua. My family is actually the turtle, but everybody comes back as the shark, too. ❤️

Do you like sharks or are you scared of them?

#bosslee

node.text:
Why network marketing?

See anyone you recognize? Comment who below. 

It’s personal development on steroids with a compensation plan attached. 

To say I was a complete disaster when I found the direct sales and network marketing profession 10 1/2 years ago is the understatement of the century.

I was an egomaniac. I had no idea how to talk to people. I didn’t know how to sell and was so driven by the idea of getting out of debt I probably would’ve done anything to save myself.

I didn’t know they were different personality types. I didn’t know about streams of income. I didn’t know about investing. I didn’t know about money hacks. I didn’t know about travel hacks. I didn’t know much about much. I was 22.

I had heard from somebody though it’s not about what you know it’s about who you know.

I’ve literally shared a stage with everyone from from Eric Thomas, to Magic Johnson, to Eric Worre to Grant Cardone, to Trent Shelton, to Kate Hudson, to Gwenyth Paltrow, to Dr. Shefali, to Pitbull to to Lisa Nichols to Gloria Mayfield Banks to Rob Dyrdek and Tony Robbins and so many more. 

Me. Small town America me. 

Why network marketing? You NEED this growth. We all do. 

#bosslee
